docs.lead_paragraph: Standing tall and somewhat aloof from each other, five miles apart on their launch pads at Cape Kennedy, two huge Saturn moon rockets await the signal to open up what NASA Administrator James Fletcher calls a "new moment in space history."

headline.main: U.S. Space Station No. 1; U.S. Space Station No. 1 A spider will go along on Skylab. Its assignment: to test spinning webs in weightlessness.

docs.abstract: article on Skylab, 1st US space station, which will be launched into earth orbit on May 14; illus
